A4.text: All three sovereign states on the eastern coast of the Baltic Sea are sometimes referred to as the 'Baltic nations', less often and in historical circumstances also as the 'Baltic republics', the 'Baltic lands', or simply the Baltics.

A5.text: All three countries are members of NATO, the European Union, the Eurozone, and the OECD.
